## Problem

`src/App.js:13` initializes `darkMode = true` and toggles it via `useState`. Refreshing the tab resets to dark. Cousin bug of #17 (favorites persistence), same fix pattern.

Also, the initial value ignores the OS-level `prefers-color-scheme` setting — a user with a system-wide light theme still gets dark on first visit.

## Fix

```js
const [darkMode, setDarkMode] = useState(() => {
  const saved = localStorage.getItem('darkMode');
  if (saved !== null) return saved === 'true';
  return window.matchMedia?.('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches ?? true;
});

useEffect(() => {
  localStorage.setItem('darkMode', String(darkMode));
}, [darkMode]);
```

The `useState` initializer runs once; the `useEffect` persists future changes.

Good first issue.

## Done when

Setting the theme persists across reloads, and first-time visitors see a theme that matches their OS preference.

